				<td colspan="2"><span>It's pretty easy to armor up fairly well on a budget, so I, too, would recommend that you save it for the important stuff, which is usually not merely l33t armor.
<br />

<br />
Adding to Klapton's list the following have been (or WOULD be) most useful to me, in no particular order:
<br />

<br />
Earring of the Solstice quest items (FT1)
<br />
Other FT items, but they're a huge money sink
<br />
Cloak of Greater Pernicity (nice bard stats)
<br />
* Vampire's Lute of Bone (stringed 2.6, primary)
<br />
Engraved Spiral Conch (brass 2.8)
<br />
* Illusion masks, particularly DE
<br />
Weight reducing backpacks
<br />
Decent haste item
<br />
Singing steel boots, helm
<br />

<br />
EDIT: * These are NO DROP and aren't otherwise attainable, but are (or would be) too useful not to mention!
<br />

<br />
<i>Denben offers a prayer to the gods to get his hands on a primary-wieldable lute one of these days.</i>
<br />

<br />
