			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: ok i got a question<a name="58990"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 25 04 4:15 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>As far as spending goes, if you have a wide budget I really reccommend the SS Breastplate, don't buy it if it's all you can afford though. Look for a Gem Inlaid Longsword and a Troubador's Mace, you want as many items with mods as possible. Getting the horn and lute are very important if you plan on AEing, also a TDoK can be fairly cheap these days and is a very important investment, solo and otherwise. Armor is not super important at this point, if you are agnostic then I really reccommend a mix of mid-range plate like the gothic that was mentioned, throw is some crustecean (stay away from the -CHA pieces obviously) and look for some good wrists like scavenger and serpentine that run cheap. Grab a Di'Zok Wristsnapper if you can, for either hand or your ranged, it's good to have. There are many diety based armors, zek being the most generous in hit points, I myself chose Tunare and found the armor to have some great cha and dex bonuses. It's all a matter of preference and money but the SS greaves have great stats and no lvl recc. although I did find the proc quite useless the rest of the stats made up for it. Don't worry too much, unless you plan on spending a huge amount of money off the bat, your gear isn't going to make a gigantic difference believe it or not, expecially if you plan on soloing a lot. Silver chitin boots are nice and you might look at something like a Crown of King Tranixx for your noggin and a black pearl chocker for your neck, I'd also take a peek at getting an iksar ceremonial bp if you can throw down for it, but don't go too crazy on regen stuff, it's all a matter of how you want to play this bard really. A decent haste item is a real must, take a look at something middle-ground like a Rune Branded Belt or a dragon sash. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
